La Argentinita is the stage name of Encarnaci&lt;U+00F3&gt;n L&lt;U+00F3&gt;pez J&lt;U+00FA&gt;lvez (Buenos Aires, March 3, 1898 &lt;U+2013&gt; New York, September 24, 1945), a Spanish dancer and singer. Among her performances was as the Butterfly in the premiere of Federico Garc&lt;U+00ED&gt;a Lorca's El maleficio de la mariposa. She partnered with Frederico Rey who, as Freddy Wittop, later enjoyed a successful and award-winning career as a theatrical costume designer.
The Spanish choreographer and ballerina Pilar L&lt;U+00F3&gt;pez J&lt;U+00FA&gt;lvez was her sister. She chose the name La Argentinita in deference to dancer La Argentina.1
